main event: A USAF liaison pilot reported seeing an unidentified flying object in Deephaven, Minnesota on May 11, 1952.
interesting points: The object was observed moving at great speed in a westerly direction for approximately 15 seconds.
The object appeared to be a 'falling star' at first, but was then determined to possess a tremendous speed and luminosity greater than a falling star.
The object carried no running or navigation lights, as required by aircraft for night flights.
The witness, a WWII liaison pilot and USAF reserve captain, was familiar with aircraft in flight.
The sighting was reported to the Air Force through an Air Intelligence Information Report.
sighted object: a spherical object with a tail
